1. Write a Java program to manage a list of 12 course codes (for example:
CS101, IT203, AI302).
• Add all course codes and display the list.
• Replace the 5th course code with a new one and confirm the change.
• Remove all course codes that begin with “IT”.
• Search for CS101 and show its position if it exists, otherwise display “Not
Found”.
• Arrange the course codes in ascending order and display the sorted list.
• Display all course codes together in a single line separated by commas.
• If the list becomes empty, display the message “EMPTY”.

SOURCE CODE:

package Exp_5_1;

import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.Collections;
import java.util.List;

public class Courses {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        // Creating list of course codes
        List<String> Courses = new ArrayList<>();
        Courses.add("CS101");
        Courses.add("IT202");
        Courses.add("AI302");
        Courses.add("EC204");
        Courses.add("IT305");
        Courses.add("CS202");
        Courses.add("AI303");
        Courses.add("EC604");
        Courses.add("IT303");
        Courses.add("AI404");
        Courses.add("EC404");
        Courses.add("IT505");

        // Display Initial List
        System.out.println("The Initial List: " + Courses);

        // Replace the element at the 5th position (index 4)
        Courses.set(4, "EC909");
        System.out.println("\nAfter Replacing the List at 5th Position: " + Courses);

        // Remove all course codes starting with "IT"
        for (int i = 0; i < Courses.size(); i++)
        {
            if (Courses.get(i).startsWith("IT"))
            {
                Courses.remove(i);
                i--; // adjust index after removal
            }
        }

        System.out.println("\nAfter Removing the Course Codes Starting with 'IT': " + Courses);

        // Search for "CS101"
        int pos = Courses.indexOf("CS101");
        if (pos != -1)
        {
            System.out.println("\nCS101 found at index: " + pos);
        }
        else
        {
            System.out.println("\nCS101 NOT FOUND");
        }

        // Sort the list in ascending order
        Collections.sort(Courses);
        System.out.println("\nSorted Course List: " + Courses);

        // Display all course codes in a single line, separated by commas
        if (Courses.isEmpty()) 
            System.out.println("EMPTY");
        else 
        	System.out.print("\n Courses Separated by Commas: ");
             System.out.println(String.join(", ", Courses));
    }
}


OUTPUT:

The Initial List: [CS101, IT202, AI302, EC204, IT305, CS202, AI303, EC604, IT303, AI404, EC404, IT505]

After Replacing the List at 5th Position: [CS101, IT202, AI302, EC204, EC909, CS202, AI303, EC604, IT303, AI404, EC404, IT505]

After Removing the Course Codes Starting with 'IT': [CS101, AI302, EC204, EC909, CS202, AI303, EC604, AI404, EC404]

CS101 found at index: 0

Sorted Course List: [AI302, AI303, AI404, CS101, CS202, EC204, EC404, EC604, EC909]

 Courses Separated by Commas: AI302, AI303, AI404, CS101, CS202, EC204, EC404, EC604, EC909
